The '''Football Association of Zambia''' (FAZ) is the governing body of [[Football_(soccer)|football]] in [[Zambia]]. It was founded in 1929, and affiliated to [[FIFA]] in 1964. It is also a member of the [[Confederation of African Football]]. It organizes the national football league and the [[Zambia national football team|national team]].
